.\" Manpage for simple_shell
.TH Simple_shell 1 "26 August 2021" "1.0" "Simple shell man page"
.SH NAME
simple_shell - UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./<NAME OF EXECUTABLE>

Compiled using: gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o <name of executable>

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell interprets and executes basic UNIX commands with arguments. It is a project assigned with certain requirements and restrictions by Holberton School with the goal of recreating a UNIX shell.

The executable displays a prompt, waits for user input, interprets it and executes if it is valid.

.SH Examples
.B ./hsh

$ ls

This will list files in the current directory

$ ls -la

This will list all files in the current directory in long format

$ echo Hello

This will print out input

$ pwd

This will print the working directory

